{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"This is my favorite place on earth,"},{"time":3698,"text":"Salar de Uyuni in Bolivia."},{"time":7792,"text":"And when it's covered\nin a thin layer of water,"},{"time":10432,"text":"it reflects the clouds."},{"time":11623,"text":"There are days when you feel\nas if you're floating among the clouds."},{"time":16552,"text":"But there are days\nwhen the horizon disappears;"},{"time":19473,"text":"there's no longer a top or a bottom."},{"time":21917,"text":"You feel immersed in something bigger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26477,"text":"It was there that one night\nI woke up from a dream,"},{"time":30445,"text":"and I saw that the stars\nwere also reflected on the water."},{"time":34043,"text":"And that wasn't a dream."},{"time":35461,"text":"It was as if you could walk\namong the stars."},{"time":38298,"text":"With every step I took,\nthe stars reverberated under my feet."},{"time":41669,"text":"It was like I was floating in the universe\namong clouds of galaxies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47779,"text":"But what's floating there today\nare not just clouds of galaxies"},{"time":51007,"text":"but also clouds of plastic."},{"time":53213,"text":"These are the footprints\nwe're leaving on the planet."},{"time":56830,"text":"They're signs of an era"},{"time":59030,"text":"in which the behavior of some humans\nis making a global impact"},{"time":63008,"text":"on our ecosystems."},{"time":66257,"text":"This era is called the Anthropocene."},{"time":69322,"text":"There's also another type\nof toxic clouds that float in the air,"},{"time":73028,"text":"like the ones that form\nfrom carbon dioxide emissions"},{"time":75988,"text":"and from the burning of fossil fuels --\noil, carbon, gas --"},{"time":79451,"text":"clouds that, when we see them,"},{"time":81665,"text":"pollute our dreams."},{"time":84055,"text":"I don't know about all of you,"},{"time":85898,"text":"but I've always dreamed of floating\namong the clouds."},{"time":88534,"text":"Maybe today we can imagine together\nother types of clouds,"},{"time":92131,"text":"clouds we can live with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94550,"text":"If you're wondering\nabout that photo, I'll explain:"},{"time":97195,"text":"it looks like a collage\nor photomontage -- something weird."},{"time":100162,"text":"No; it's reality."},{"time":101542,"text":"But sometimes I ask myself:\nWhat is reality?"},{"time":104092,"text":"According to Alexander Kluge:"},{"time":105785,"text":"\"Human beings are not\ninterested in reality."},{"time":108373,"text":"They can’t be; it’s part\nof the human essence."},{"time":111655,"text":"They have desires."},{"time":113977,"text":"These desires are totally opposed\nto any form of reality."},{"time":117405,"text":"They prefer to lie"},{"time":119121,"text":"than to become divorced\nfrom their desires.\""},{"time":122519,"text":"But how can we learn\nto float among the clouds?"},{"time":126997,"text":"As an artist, I thought we could start\nbuilding a flying museum."},{"time":132458,"text":"You're probably wondering:\nWith plastic bags?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":134626,"text":"In 2007, with a community of people\nall over the world,"},{"time":137590,"text":"we began to collect used plastic bags --"},{"time":140492,"text":"not new ones."},{"time":142080,"text":"And we washed them,"},{"time":144865,"text":"we cut them up,"},{"time":146322,"text":"we glued them together,"},{"time":147773,"text":"and we began to draw on them,"},{"time":149741,"text":"creating a huge canvas."},{"time":151588,"text":"We made a collection of drawings,"},{"time":153612,"text":"of personal stories"},{"time":154914,"text":"and of friendships."},{"time":156542,"text":"And when you join them,"},{"time":158378,"text":"bend them and fold them,"},{"time":160402,"text":"it creates a space full of air."},{"time":162797,"text":"When the sun comes up from the horizon,"},{"time":166319,"text":"the museum rises up to the sky."},{"time":168197,"text":"That's why we call it,\n\"The Aero-Solar Museum.\""},{"time":170532,"text":"And from this simple idea,"},{"time":171873,"text":"we learned how to float in the air\nin a radically new way,"},{"time":174784,"text":"without using any type of fuel."},{"time":177028,"text":"The difference in temperature\nbetween the interior and the exterior"},{"time":180743,"text":"is what makes us rise up."},{"time":182767,"text":"That way,"},{"time":185316,"text":"we don't use fossil fuels\nor helium or hydrogen;"},{"time":189503,"text":"we don't use solar panels"},{"time":191693,"text":"or batteries or motors."},{"time":194248,"text":"We discovered a way that's simple,\nclean and accessible to the whole world"},{"time":199562,"text":"to lift ourselves up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200976,"text":"I remember when I was at NASA in 2009\nwith 120 engineers."},{"time":206383,"text":"You guys know, too,\nwhen you go up in a plane,"},{"time":209019,"text":"the control panels are gigantic."},{"time":211106,"text":"And what we're doing is really complex,"},{"time":214746,"text":"and when I started coming in\nwith the plastic bags, saying,"},{"time":217742,"text":"\"But we have a different way ...\""},{"time":219425,"text":"people had a hard time\nunderstanding the concept."},{"time":221789,"text":"Seeing the power of this idea,"},{"time":223357,"text":"we started to initiate a new era;"},{"time":225020,"text":"one that would leave behind\nthe violence of the Anthropocene"},{"time":228018,"text":"and give way to a new era,"},{"time":229529,"text":"which we call the \"Aerocene\" --"},{"time":231623,"text":"an era of ecological awareness,"},{"time":234463,"text":"in which we learn to float together,\nlive together in the air,"},{"time":237664,"text":"and come to an ethical commitment"},{"time":239353,"text":"with the atmosphere and with planet earth."},{"time":242477,"text":"That's why I've brought\nthis backpack today."},{"time":244622,"text":"Let's see ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254996,"text":"OK. This is a balloon\nthat we also refer to as a sculpture."},{"time":258408,"text":"And if it's sunny out tomorrow,\nwe can go out and fly --"},{"time":261322,"text":"though, no, the weather\nin Vancouver isn't --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":263658,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":265138,"text":"it's not very ..."},{"time":267230,"text":"very favorable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269526,"text":"So, what other features does it have?"},{"time":271623,"text":"It has sensors that, when it moves,"},{"time":274010,"text":"make sort of drawings in the air."},{"time":277121,"text":"It also has other sensors."},{"time":278717,"text":"I always think that first\nyou have to feel it,"},{"time":280941,"text":"and then you can measure it;"},{"time":283055,"text":"you need to hear the sounds\nof the atmosphere,"},{"time":285349,"text":"of the climate, of the hot air,"},{"time":286907,"text":"in order to then measure the ozone,"},{"time":289002,"text":"the carbon dioxide."},{"time":290819,"text":"We're developing these sensors"},{"time":292384,"text":"together with different communities\nall over the world"},{"time":295085,"text":"in order to reconnect with the climate,\nthe temperature and the environment,"},{"time":298914,"text":"because there are other\nspecies in the air;"},{"time":301152,"text":"in these excursions\ntowards the atmosphere,"},{"time":303224,"text":"we're not alone."},{"time":304411,"text":"The air is full of clouds of life."},{"time":306195,"text":"We live at the bottom of an ocean of air."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309055,"text":"And this same sculpture,"},{"time":312702,"text":"this exact one in my hands,"},{"time":314084,"text":"flew 375 miles -- 12 hours --\nfrom Germany to Poland,"},{"time":316885,"text":"on a fuel-free trip."},{"time":318087,"text":"But it wasn't free from crossing borders."},{"time":320264,"text":"The trip was much more complicated\nthan what we imagined;"},{"time":323154,"text":"air space is as regulated and militarized"},{"time":325638,"text":"as land space."},{"time":327423,"text":"To fly using the winds,\nthe heat of the sun"},{"time":329896,"text":"and the radiant energy of the earth"},{"time":331658,"text":"is complex and beautiful."},{"time":333943,"text":"But even more complex\nwill be getting the permits"},{"time":336341,"text":"to cross the air space\nof each of the different countries"},{"time":339405,"text":"that we fly over using wind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341794,"text":"At COP21, the Paris Climate Conference,"},{"time":345621,"text":"we presented these spherical sculptures"},{"time":347767,"text":"that could transport us\nall over the world."},{"time":350317,"text":"But how can we fly using the wind\nto arrive at our destination?"},{"time":354223,"text":"Together with MIT, we developed a program"},{"time":356696,"text":"that predicts how we can navigate\nthe wind highways."},{"time":359800,"text":"For example, if I had to return\nto Berlin from Vancouver,"},{"time":363845,"text":"the first thing I would need to do\nis choose an altitude."},{"time":366560,"text":"At different altitudes,\nthere are different directions"},{"time":369892,"text":"and different speeds."},{"time":372035,"text":"The red line is tomorrow\nand the orange, the day after tomorrow."},{"time":375182,"text":"And there it goes."},{"time":376374,"text":"You can see, the best day\nto fly back to Berlin --"},{"time":380594,"text":"so now, traveling using only wind --"},{"time":384114,"text":"is in six days."},{"time":385579,"text":"And we can get to 105 miles\nfrom the center of Berlin"},{"time":388661,"text":"without burning a single drop of fuel,"},{"time":390594,"text":"being transported only by wind currents."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393505,"text":"So we thought that these trajectories\nthat we drew with the wind"},{"time":397407,"text":"could become signatures, declaring\n\"Independence from Fossil Fuels Day.\""},{"time":402688,"text":"More and more of us\nare experiencing the air"},{"time":405402,"text":"in a different way."},{"time":407139,"text":"You're all familiar with Earth Day."},{"time":409284,"text":"We think we should also celebrate Air Day:"},{"time":412048,"text":"it's a pact that we make with the earth,"},{"time":414058,"text":"an ethical commitment to the atmosphere."},{"time":417853,"text":"But let's keep thinking and dreaming."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419929,"text":"We've learned that the bigger\nthe sculptures are,"},{"time":424199,"text":"the more weight they can lift."},{"time":426881,"text":"Remember,"},{"time":428647,"text":"they rise up only with hot air\nthat's been heated by the sun."},{"time":434148,"text":"Using this approach, we can learn\nto build gardens in the air."},{"time":437759,"text":"Could we one day live in a garden\nthe size of the earth?"},{"time":441448,"text":"Could we live in an ecosystem\nfloating among the clouds?"},{"time":445444,"text":"Answering these questions\nisn't just a technological challenge;"},{"time":449095,"text":"it's a way to reexamine\nthe freedom of movement between countries,"},{"time":454302,"text":"and of overcoming the political,\nsocial, cultural and military restrictions"},{"time":458113,"text":"of contemporary societies."},{"time":459825,"text":"Because in the end,"},{"time":461522,"text":"the air belongs to everybody"},{"time":463243,"text":"and doesn't answer to any government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466544,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":473388,"text":"And like we said earlier,"},{"time":474733,"text":"our imagination is the force\nthat allows us to create these places."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478888,"text":"This is an installation I did"},{"time":480603,"text":"at the Metropolitan Museum\nof Art in New York."},{"time":483034,"text":"It asks the question:"},{"time":484335,"text":"What might these transnational\nspaces be like?"},{"time":487103,"text":"And once we inhabit those spaces,\nwe need to learn how to move within them,"},{"time":492039,"text":"to walk among the clouds,"},{"time":494571,"text":"where every movement affects\neveryone else's movements;"},{"time":497968,"text":"the body weight and proximity\nbetween people"},{"time":501169,"text":"will cause the space to expand ..."},{"time":503217,"text":"or contract."},{"time":506430,"text":"There we are, suspended\n72 feet in the air."},{"time":509549,"text":"When two or more people\nget too close together,"},{"time":512787,"text":"even those farthest away are affected --"},{"time":516216,"text":"everyone falls to the same spot."},{"time":518541,"text":"These are fragile ecosystems."},{"time":521943,"text":"And it's between these spheres\nthat we build nets that connect us."},{"time":526313,"text":"There are moments\nwhen we have to face the void,"},{"time":529755,"text":"and fear can paralyze us."},{"time":532459,"text":"One of the most beautiful things\nabout this exhibit"},{"time":534936,"text":"is the sense of solidarity generated"},{"time":536737,"text":"when we face these new \"aero-graphs.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":539893,"text":"Finally,"},{"time":541473,"text":"let me tell you one last story."},{"time":543497,"text":"On July 16, 1945,"},{"time":545695,"text":"on the White Sands of New Mexico,"},{"time":547719,"text":"an atomic bomb was detonated\nfor the first time."},{"time":551703,"text":"As a result of this explosion,"},{"time":553335,"text":"a cloud of radioactive particles\ndisseminated all over the earth,"},{"time":557933,"text":"marking the beginning\nof the Anthropocene era."},{"time":561540,"text":"Seventy years later, on November 8, 2015,"},{"time":564761,"text":"in the same place,"},{"time":566339,"text":"another event occurred."},{"time":568561,"text":"For the first time in history,"},{"time":570339,"text":"we lifted a person into the air\nusing only the sun,"},{"time":573521,"text":"without burning any fossil fuels."},{"time":576318,"text":"As the sun rose up above the horizon,"},{"time":578844,"text":"we rose up, too,"},{"time":580505,"text":"silently,"},{"time":582193,"text":"slowly,"},{"time":583384,"text":"with no explosions."},{"time":584914,"text":"We felt as if gravity had been inverted;"},{"time":588125,"text":"it wasn't pulling us\ntoward the center of the earth,"},{"time":590975,"text":"but toward the universe."},{"time":593381,"text":"If Neil Armstrong said,\nwhen he walked on the moon,"},{"time":596040,"text":"\"That's one small step for man,"},{"time":597830,"text":"one giant leap for mankind,\""},{"time":600631,"text":"perhaps what we ought to ask ourselves is:"},{"time":602655,"text":"What steps do we need to take today?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":605379,"text":"In the Aerocene era,"},{"time":607835,"text":"our steps are much smaller,\nbut radically different;"},{"time":612060,"text":"they're steps that began with a bag\nfull of air and wishes,"},{"time":617280,"text":"but that can carry us\nto independence from fossil fuels"},{"time":621234,"text":"and the opportunity to celebrate Air Day;"},{"time":623267,"text":"steps that won't leave footprints\non other planets"},{"time":626608,"text":"until we've learned to walk\nin the atmosphere of this one."},{"time":630883,"text":"The landscapes are tiny"},{"time":632962,"text":"and the steps are tiny,"},{"time":634556,"text":"but I hope we can take them together."},{"time":636978,"text":"And I'm sure that these steps will lead us\nmuch further than the moon,"},{"time":640826,"text":"so we can learn to float\nwith our feet on the ground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644750,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645936,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}